Hi Heath,

Thank you so much.

I just had a meeting with Sarah and noticed that the podcasts listed here (https://www.msaustralia.org.au/nmosd-your-way/). Is there any chance we could embed them onto the website instead? This website has them embedded (https://nmosdyourwaypodcastaustralia.podigee.io/) and if you click the share button it looks like we could do the same. Apologies, that was my fault for providing the wrong link.

It also looks like they have a new episode listed (Taking back control). Could we add that to our website as this:

Episode 6:

Taking back control

Guest: Dr Therese Burke

Registered Nurse

Thank you again. I apologise for the all the back and forth.

Best wishes,

Tennille

Hi Heath,

I hope you had a lovely weekend. Thanks for getting this together so quickly.

I made same minor changes (this has resulted in the pages being published but that's okay). I realised that the supports and services/resources duplicated each other on the main page so I removed that from the bottom. I also realised that I had the name of the podcast the wrong way around (It's NMOSD Your Way, not Your Way NMOSD). I updated that too, but would you mind updating the URL to reflect that?

I really like how the "Helpful Links and Resources" looks on the main NMOSD page. Are you able to replicate that for the podcast page too (without the link to the podcasts)? That'll reduce the gap where the host is mentioned and make those resources more accessible again. Perhaps we could use the attached image to fill the gap next to the host section?

I also just discovered that there are links to subscribe to these podcasts on different platforms (https://nmosdyourwaypodcastaustralia.podigee.io/#subscribe). Is there any chance you could please include a section at the bottom of the podcast page for this? We have permission to use this material on our website.

Thank you again for all your help on this.

Best wishes,

Tennille
